description: Lists all subscribers for the specific Amazon Security Lake account ID. You can retrieve a list of subscriptions associated with a specific organization or Amazon Web Services account.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If nextToken is returned, there are more results available. You can repeat the call using the returned token to retrieve the next page.

nested_items.name: subscribers
nested_items.description: The subscribers available for the specified Security Lake account ID.

nested_items.name: accessTypes
nested_items.description: You can choose to notify subscribers of new objects with an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) queue or through messaging to an HTTPS endpoint provided by the subscriber.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time when the subscriber was created.

nested_items.name: resourceShareArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) which uniquely defines the Amazon Web Services RAM resource share. Before accepting the RAM resource share invitation, you can view details related to the RAM resource share.

nested_items.name: resourceShareName
nested_items.description: The name of the resource share.

nested_items.name: roleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) specifying the role of the subscriber.

nested_items.name: s3BucketArn
nested_items.description: The ARN for the Amazon S3 bucket.

nested_items.name: sources
nested_items.description: Amazon Security Lake supports log and event collection for natively supported Amazon Web Services services. For more information, see the Amazon Security Lake User Guide.

nested_items.name: awsLogSource
nested_items.description: Amazon Security Lake supports log and event collection for natively supported Amazon Web Services services. For more information, see the Amazon Security Lake User Guide.

nested_items.name: sourceName
nested_items.description: The name for a Amazon Web Services source. This must be a Regionally unique value.

nested_items.name: sourceVersion
nested_items.description: The version for a Amazon Web Services source. This must be a Regionally unique value.

nested_items.name: customLogSource
nested_items.description: Amazon Security Lake supports custom source types. For more information, see the Amazon Security Lake User Guide.

nested_items.name: attributes
nested_items.description: The attributes of a third-party custom source.

nested_items.name: crawlerArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the Glue crawler.

nested_items.name: databaseArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the Glue database where results are written, such as: arn:aws:daylight:us-east-1::database/sometable/*.

nested_items.name: tableArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the Glue table.

nested_items.name: location
nested_items.description: The location of the partition in the Amazon S3 bucket for Security Lake.

nested_items.name: roleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the IAM role to be used by the entity putting logs into your custom source partition. Security Lake will apply the correct access policies to this role, but you must first manually create the trust policy for this role. The IAM role name must start with the text --Security Lake'. The IAM role must trust the logProviderAccountId to assume the role.

nested_items.name: sourceName
nested_items.description: The name for a third-party custom source. This must be a Regionally unique value.

nested_items.name: sourceVersion
nested_items.description: The version for a third-party custom source. This must be a Regionally unique value.

nested_items.name: subscriberArn
nested_items.description: The subscriber ARN of the Amazon Security Lake subscriber account.

nested_items.name: subscriberDescription
nested_items.description: The subscriber descriptions for a subscriber account. The description for a subscriber includes subscriberName, accountID, externalID, and subscriberId.

nested_items.name: subscriberEndpoint
nested_items.description: The subscriber endpoint to which exception messages are posted.

nested_items.name: subscriberId
nested_items.description: The subscriber ID of the Amazon Security Lake subscriber account.

nested_items.name: subscriberIdentity
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services identity used to access your data.

nested_items.name: externalId
nested_items.description: The external ID used to establish trust relationship with the Amazon Web Services identity.

nested_items.name: principal
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services identity principal.

nested_items.name: subscriberName
nested_items.description: The name of your Amazon Security Lake subscriber account.

nested_items.name: subscriberStatus
nested_items.description: The subscriber status of the Amazon Security Lake subscriber account.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time when the subscriber was last updated.
